1.) Make an RDS database
	-mysql
	-set admin passwords
2.) Make a backend image with the script file 
3.) Make a launch config using the background image and set up an auto scaling group
4.)set up a launch balancer and then connect it to your back end scaling group,
5.)make a front end image also using the script file
6.)Set up a front end launch config using the front end image and set up an auto scaling group
7.)set up a load balancer for my front end and connect it to the front end scaling groups.

This should now keep 1 instance up and if the cpu usage exceeds 30% then one more vm will be produced